5. Sensor Utilization
SunSafe leverages three key smartphone sensors plus external APIs:

5.1 Ambient Light Sensor
Purpose: Detect sunlight exposure intensity and duration.

How it works: Measures illuminance in lux. Direct sunlight typically reads 30,000-100,000+ lux.

Implementation:

Continuous background monitoring (with user permission).

Compares readings against threshold to determine "in sun" vs. "in shade/indoors."

Accumulates time when lux > 10,000 (configurable).

Challenges: Sensor placement (phone in pocket vs. in hand). Mitigation: User can manually log or use smartwatch companion.

5.2 GPS (Global Positioning System)
Purpose: Determine user location to fetch local UV index.

How it works: Uses network location (low power) for regular updates; GPS (high accuracy) when app active.

Implementation:

Gets latitude/longitude coordinates.

Sends location to UV API (OpenUV, OpenWeatherMap, etc.).

Caches UV data for current location to minimize API calls.

Privacy: Location data never leaves device unencrypted; anonymized if used for community features.

5.3 Camera (Optional)
Purpose: Skin self-assessment and sunscreen reminder photos.

Implementation:

Users can photograph skin spots for tracking changes over time.

Photos stored locally with optional cloud backup (encrypted).

Used for "sunscreen check" – photo of applied sunscreen to confirm usage.

5.4 Accelerometer (Supporting)
Purpose: Detect outdoor activity context.

Implementation:

Differentiates between stationary (lying on beach) vs. moving (walking).

Adjusts exposure calculation based on activity level (moving = more exposure due to angle changes).

6. Core Features
6.1 Automatic Exposure Tracking
Background monitoring using ambient light sensor.

Daily exposure timeline showing when and where sun exposure occurred.

Manual override option for times when phone isn't with user.

6.2 Personalized Safe Limit Calculator
Input: Fitzpatrick skin type (I-VI), sunscreen SPF, application frequency.

Output: Maximum safe minutes before burning at current UV index.

Dynamic adjustment as UV index changes throughout the day.

6.3 Smart Alerts & Reminders
Pre-Exposure: "UV index is High today. Apply SPF 30+ before going out."

Limit Warning: "You've reached 80% of your safe limit. Reapply sunscreen or seek shade."

Reapplication: "2 hours since last application. Time to reapply!"

After-Sun Care: "You exceeded your limit today. Apply soothing after-sun lotion."

6.4 Vitamin D Optimizer
Calculates optimal sun time for vitamin D synthesis based on:

Skin type (darker skin requires longer exposure).

UV index (too high = burn risk, too low = no vitamin D production).

Time of day (best between 10 AM - 3 PM).

Balances burn prevention with vitamin D needs.

6.5 Historical Trends & Analytics
Daily, weekly, monthly exposure summaries.

Heat map calendar showing high-exposure days.

Correlation with sunburn incidents (user-reported).

Long-term skin health trends.

6.6 Location-Based UV Forecasting
5-day UV forecast for current location.

Search UV forecast for travel destinations.

Peak UV hours highlighted daily.

6.7 PDF Report Generation
Export dermatologist-friendly report including:

Exposure history (last 30/90 days).

Sunburn incidents.

Skin photos (if taken).

Average daily UV exposure.

6.8 Child/Family Profiles
Parents can create profiles for children.

Separate safe limits based on child's skin type.

Notifications sent to parent's phone.

