12. Testing Strategy
Unit Testing
Exposure Calculation: Test algorithm with various UV indices and skin types.

Safe Limit Logic: Verify limits change correctly with inputs.

Date/Time Handling: Ensure accurate accumulation across days.

Integration Testing
Sensor Data Flow: Light sensor → database → UI.

API Integration: Mock API responses, test caching.

Notification System: Verify triggers fire at correct thresholds.

Device Testing
Test on minimum 5 physical devices with varying:

Android versions (10-15)

Screen sizes (small phone to tablet)

Sensor quality (budget to flagship)

Manufacturers (Samsung, Xiaomi, Google, Tecno)

User Acceptance Testing
10-15 test users with different skin types.

Collect feedback on alert timing and accuracy.

Validate UV index correlation with real conditions.

13. Constraints & Limitations
Technical Constraints
Constraint	Impact	Mitigation
Light sensor unavailable on some budget phones	Cannot auto-track	Manual logging option
Light sensor accuracy varies	False positives/negatives	Calibration + user adjustments
Battery drain from continuous sensing	User may disable	Optimize sampling rate; use Motion传感器 to detect outdoor activity before sampling
GPS usage drains battery	Location-based UV may be disabled	Cache UV data; use network location when possible
API rate limits	Free UV APIs have daily limits	Cache aggressively; fallback to estimated UV
Functional Limitations
Phone Placement: If phone is in bag/pocket, light sensor won't detect sun.

Indoor UV: Windows block some UVB but not UVA – app focuses on outdoor.

Cloud Cover: API provides UV forecast; real-time sensor may show lower readings.

Medical Accuracy: App provides estimates, not medical devices. Disclaimers required.

